    "body": "I interrupted geth with a Cntrl-c, and got the response:\n\n```\nI0226 22:38:55.942523   10784 blockchain.go:1243] imported 1 block(s) (0 queued 0 ignored) including 0 txs in 3.5022ms. #1065039 [164c192a / 164c192a]\nI0226 22:39:16.176947   10784 blockchain.go:1243] imported 1 block(s) (0 queued 0 ignored) including 1 txs in 5.0033ms. #1065040 [2632be30 / 2632be30]\nI0227 17:39:05.800486   10784 cmd.go:123] Got interrupt, shutting down...\n```\n\nBut geth didn't terminate, it was stuck at that position. That is, I didn't get back to the DOC prompt. Pressing CTRL-C again, produced  the following:\n\n```\nI0227 17:42:19.472916   10784 cmd.go:129] Already shutting down, please be patient.\nI0227 17:42:19.478055   10784 cmd.go:130] Interrupt 9 more times to induce panic.\n```\n\nAfter a while (couple of minutes), I was no longer patient, and pressed additional CTRL-C. See [geth panic output 2016-02-27](https://gist.github.com/larspensjo/93f9d8fb7f6dec30e742) with output from the panic statement.\n",
